storyInfo: The Sarkaz tighten their control of the city. A group of Sarkaz mercenaries enter the factory, preparing to execute Catherine and any others who knew about the supply lines.

attributes.content: You saw it, Morgan?
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: The guards at the warehouse were so nervous that they didn't even see me coming.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Alright, alright, you win today. Take your jerky.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Ha, knew you'd be cross. Next time you can come with, and loser has to keep guard.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: ...They're staring at us.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Who?
attributes.name: Indra
Indra
attributes.content: What are you stari—

attributes.name: Indra
attributes.content: What's this about...? Get outta the way, already. I need a drink from the kitchen. Thirsty after all that work.
attributes.joined: What are you stari—What's this about...? Get outta the way, already. I need a drink from the kitchen. Thirsty after all that work.

attributes.content: You shouldn't have done that.
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: You mean lure away the Sarkaz patrol, giving your people a chance to escape the warehouse?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: Funny way to say 'thank you'? Or did I hear you wrong?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Our comrades in Sudean are grateful, and so are we. The mission went well. But why did you have to burn the warehouse?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: It belonged to a Victorian merchant, not the Sarkaz! The Sarkaz were just occupying it.
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: Ha. Those fat cats are as cowardly as they are greedy. They want to help the Sarkaz, I'm happy to make them suffer for it.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: You do understand that you're just driving them into the arms of the Sarkaz?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: Even better. More than just warehouses to burn for those traitors.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: That's gangster talk, not the way of the Self-Salvation Corps.
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: Do you still insist on working with these people, Lady Isabelle?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: My name is Dagda here.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Er...
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: It's just, Lady Isa—Dagda. When Lady Allerdale introduced you and Her Highness to us, we thought...
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: Siege told you on day one that it was the Glasgow Gang working with the Corps, not Her Highness Alexandrina and the Knight of the Tower.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Do you really want to see a hoodlum lead us, even take the throne?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: What shit-for-brains gives you the right to say that about Vina?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Sword back in its place, Morgan! We're on their ground!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Many of us would rather follow you and Cumberland...
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: Stuff it! I-I mean, you've said your piece. As long as we still stand together, you should not speak ill of our fellows.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Sorry, I spoke out of turn.
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: You shouldn't have stopped me.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: And let you make a mess for Vina to clean up? Not to mention the bunny and the Doctor from Rhodes Island. Next time, think about your company before you lose your head.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Ha... never thought the day would come that you'd be the one talking to me about losing my head.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Gotta change, and adapt to the environment. Look how Dagda is doing.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Don't say that, it feels weird.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: You think I wanna congratulate you? Living your way doesn't feel too nice.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: But there's one thing the past couple days've taught me, Morgan. We have to adapt to keep up with Vina.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: ...Hmph.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Here, your jerky. Neither of us won the day.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Keep it. I've got no appetite.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: I've been thinking, Hannah... is this the kind of life that Vina wants? Since when did nobles and merchants give her the respect she deserves?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: You're not thinking from the right angle.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: They'll realize Vina is a good leader. And the respect Vina gets, she would've earned herself.
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Ah, Lady Allerdale! Finally!
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: Sorry, I've been busy.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: I heard you were looking for a buyer for the Steam Armor?
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: ...The news reached you quickly.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Only rumors, only rumors. A friend mentioned that a suit of Steam Armor from Londinium might appear on the market.
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: But the transaction fell through at the last minute.
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: ...I see.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: I would not recommend that you sell something so valuable too easily. It's hard to get a good price under current market conditions.
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: Thank you for the advice. I'm just trying to do something useful with what little assets my family has left.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: I understand. What little money we have means nothing to the Sarkaz.
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: Has the banquet not yet started? There's no need to wait for me.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: We can't have that now. You've been the pillar of Central Londinium for ages. It's all thanks to you that we're alive today.
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: How is one even supposed to negotiate with a bunch of lunatics who don't care about money?
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: You flatter me, sir. I'm just a nobody who spoke up a few times at the unjust treatment that those like you have received.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Now, now, don't say that. House Cumberland will undoubtedly rise again under your leadership!
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: Yes, the past is the past now.
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: When Londinium knows peace again—not to say that she's not at peace right now, of course!
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: In any case, House Cumberland will have our gratitude.
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: Lt. Colonel Lettou is here!
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: We salute you!
attributes.name: Slimy Noble & Astute Noble

attributes.content: It's an honor, Lt. Colonel. You have not graced us with your presence for many nights.
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: We are most grateful for your efforts to keep the peace!
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: I've come into a few bottles of excellent wine.
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: They may not have been so impressive in the old days, but in times like these they are a rarity. I'll have my butler bring them to your residence.
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: Ladies and gentlemen...
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: There will be no more banquets, from this day forth.
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: The Military Commission will be interviewing you soon. Good luck.
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: ...Huh?
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: Wait, no! What do you mean?
attributes.name: Slimy Noble

attributes.content: Lt. Colonel Lettou! Lt. Colonel Lettou!
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: Lady Allerdale, you must speak to Lt. Colonel Lettou! This is serious! P-People will die!
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: Lt. Colonel! Please don't go!
attributes.name: Astute Noble

attributes.content: Miss, this is...
attributes.name: Ailshie

attributes.content: The Sarkaz have been biding their time. They let these fools wallow in luxury in order to keep the dukes from coming together.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: There is nothing any given duke would like more than to become the master of Victoria.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: At the center of Victorian high society is Londinium, and whomever makes an enemy of Londinium nobility makes an enemy of the entire state.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Such an offense against Victoria would have forced the dukes to put aside their individual interests and join forces to march on Londinium.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: But the Sarkaz don't care anymore.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: They've achieved their goal.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Some think what befell Londinium the past few years a disaster. But now—
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: War has truly come.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: What about us, then?
attributes.name: Ailshie

attributes.content: Could you talk to Lt. Colonel Lettou, as the nobles suggested? You might...
attributes.name: Ailshie

attributes.content: They called me 'pillar'. But whom amongst them set foot in Cumberland Manor before the Sarkaz took control of Londinium?
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Which of the Duke's true friends participated in these pretentious banquets?
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: I'm simply a figurehead for nobles who lack chips on their side, or those who are trying to protect themselves.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: They flocked to the Cumberland banner, so Cumberland may take the fall for them.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: So what you mean is...
attributes.name: Ailshie

attributes.content: Let's go, Ailshie. Inform our Self-Salvation Corps and Rhodes Islander friends to evacuate the ducal manor immediately. It is no longer safe.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: We'll take one last look at our ancestral home.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Allerdale.
attributes.name: Noble?

attributes.content: You are...
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: A letter from the duke.
attributes.name: Noble?

attributes.content: A few days in Auchterigg, then Highbury. Look at all those factories and houses packed tight together. Never seen a place so cramped.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Can we go back to Central Londinium after this mission, Captain?
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: And do what? I don't know what Manfred was thinking, hiring kids like you who've barely taken a life before...
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: I'm not a kid! I did a lot of jobs back in Columbia with Grimm, when he was still around!
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: Grimm, eh...? I have babysit now because he got himself killed in Sudean. I should've taken his head and nabbed the bounty beforehand.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Er... weren't you friends?
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: It's not my job to teach you how to be a mercenary, kid. But it is yours to read the map. Where do we go next?
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Munitions Factory No. 11 is just ahead.
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: General Manfred gave us a pretty long list... these are all older workers who know something, right? Just take them somewhere with no witnesses and kill them?
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: I would kill everyone in the factory, if it were up to me.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: All that crap about killing only the ones who know anything... does he have any idea how much trouble that is?
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Well, he's the boss.
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: Whatever. Put away the list and let's go.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Feist!
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Patto.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: It's been a year. I missed you.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Sorry, I should have tried to send word.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Never mind that. I'm so glad to see you. For the past year, I've been telling everyone that you'd definitely come back alive.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Remember that vent over there? There's a bit of a platform outside the other end of it.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: A few years ago, you said you would jump off it and onto the factory next door.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: We were scared out of our minds. It was what, more than thirty meters off the ground? Fall, and you'd be dead for sure.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: But you dared to jump. And then... Tommy jumped, Day jumped, and in the end I jumped too.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Whenever they ask me if I think you're dead, I tell them to look up at the vent.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Haha... we weren't afraid of anything, were we?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: So these are your Self-Salvation Corps friends?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Looks well-read to me.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: I heard there were all kinds in the Corps. Guess the rumors are true.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: The Doctor is definitely well-read.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: You have partners?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: It's sounding more and more like the real deal, isn't it?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Haha.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: So, why have you come back? Anything I can help with?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: I—
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Patto!
attributes.name: Catherine
Londinium Worker
attributes.content: Ca—

attributes.name: Londinium Worker
attributes.content: Catherine... I'm sorry.
Get back to work.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Yes, ma'am.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: But Feist is back, isn't he? He's not going anywhere?
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Don't you worry about him right now. As for your friend, we should talk somewhere else.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Don't blame Catherine, Feist.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: She's been protecting us from the Sarkaz for the past year. It's thanks to her that we haven't lost anybody.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: There was one time when things got really bad, and she called on the leader of the Defense Forces to mediate.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: But the Sarkaz have been putting more pressure on us, on Catherine.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: I know, Patto.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I don't blame Granny one bit.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: When I joined the Corps and truly understood what I was facing...
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I knew what a difficult decision Granny had to make.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Alright, talk. What did you come back for?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: We're looking for something.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Something?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Yes. A hidden Sarkaz supply line that's fueling their mad war.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: We're certain the line ends here in the industrial district.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: We need to find it.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.options: Feist says no one knows the district better.

attributes.content: No one knows the district better than you, Granny. I'm sure you can help.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: That's why I came to you.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Flattering me won't do you any good.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Yes, we won't cause any trouble for the factory.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Why do you think I would help you?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Maybe I already told Patto to call the Sarkaz mercenaries.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: If that's the case... I'll have to flee with the others.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Tell me, how many died in that incident you caused in Sudean?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Do you remember their names? Their faces? Do you remember what they looked like when they died? Their last words?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Don't rush your answer, Feist. And don't try to bluff your way through it.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I don't know what this 'Doctor' of yours thinks, but I know you. You think you're smart, but being smart isn't enough to fool death.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Catherine! A bunch of Sarkaz just showed up at the door...
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: Doctor, we need to get out of here—
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: They say Lt. Colonel Lettou, a Defense Force officer, wants to see you. You're to be escorted.
attributes.name: Londinium Worker

attributes.content: ...What?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: George, watch these two and make sure they stay put.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Care for a smoke?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Don't bother trying to butter me up.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Lt. Colonel Lettou wants to see me?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: We've been meeting our targets. Nothing for him to worry about.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Whatever. He wants to see you. Come with us.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Give me a minute. I have something to take care of first.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: We're not asking, old bag.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: I have to put someone in charge. This is very sudden, after all.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: We can wait a little bit... can't we?
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: (Whisper) I don't think the General wants a scene.
attributes.name: Paprika

attributes.content: Ugh. You have ten minutes.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary Captain

attributes.content: Good enough.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Granny, why are they looking for you?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: None of your business.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: But—
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Shut up and come with me.
attributes.name: Catherine
